Thus, the sine and cosine functions are periodic according to the following definition: A
function f is periodic if there is a positive number p such that f 1t ! p 2 " f 1t 2 for every t.
The least such positive number (if it exists) is the period of f. If f has period p, then the
graph of f on any interval of length p is called one complete period of f.
